Identifiers in java :
=====================

Defination : it is any name, it can be variable name or class name or method name or object name or package name.
Rules :
i) spaces cannot be used.
int roll no = 101;  //not applicable
int roll_no = 101; //applicable

ii) only undersocre(_) and dollar($) sign can be used in identifier name,

iii) Integer value cannot be used at first position but can be used after first character.
int 1roll_no = 100;     //not applicable
int roll_no1 = 100;     //applicable

iv) Reserved words cannot be used as an identifier name
int public = 101    //not applicable
int public1 = 101   //applicable because after in name we used 1